Package: CorpusBiblioExtractor
Title: Exhaustive Biblioshiny Sweeps and UI-Metadata Extraction from a Bibliographic Corpus
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Miguel Jesus", "Diaz Macedo", email = "miguel.diazmacedo@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Drives 'bibliometrix' directly (no GUI, no Python) to run the full
    Cartesian sweep of the biblioshiny "Main Configuration" selectors over a
    bibliographic corpus, materialising every output asset (tables as .xlsx,
    static figures as .png, interactive networks and Sankeys as .html, Pajek
    .net), a per-run self-contained HTML viewer, and an AST-based extractor of
    the biblioshiny UI metadata straight from its source code. This is a
    personal portfolio project: it is beta and intended to stay beta, it is
    pinned to the package versions it was tested against, and it offers no
    support and accepts no pull requests. See README, DISCLAIMER and NOTICE.
    Built on, requiring, and interoperable with the GPL-3 'bibliometrix' package
    and its 'biblioshiny' interface (Aria and Cuccurullo); attribution in NOTICE.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Language: en
